SHANE SMITH: So this is our
chief of police, and he's

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:26.700
breaking in to the North
Korean camp.

00:02:26.700 --> 00:02:29.996
I love him.

00:02:29.996 --> 00:02:31.960
RODION MIKHAILOV:
[SPEAKING RUSSIAN]

00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:33.433
SHANE SMITH: [LAUGH]

00:02:33.433 --> 00:02:37.380
I love this guy so much.

00:02:37.380 --> 00:02:40.180
This was a whole
Korean village.

00:02:40.180 --> 00:02:42.090
SIMON OSTROVSKY: They had a
sign here that said, "Kim

00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:44.500
Il-Sung lives with
us forever."

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:46.690
SHANE SMITH: Because, I guess,
that there have been some

00:02:46.690 --> 00:02:48.390
people who came--

00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:50.560
Simon, who's with us,
being one of them--

00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:51.970
they've knocked down the camp.

00:02:51.970 --> 00:02:53.530
And they've moved on
to the next village

00:02:53.530 --> 00:02:55.850
down the train line.

00:02:55.850 --> 00:02:58.180
SIMON OSTROVSKY: This used to
have a slogan on it that said,

00:02:58.180 --> 00:03:01.630
"laboratory of Kim Il-Sung's
theory." So they've given it

00:03:01.630 --> 00:03:03.900
over to an entrepreneur
to take down.

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:06.940
And then his benefit is he gets
to sell the spare parts

00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:08.970
and metal and stuff like that.

00:03:08.970 --> 00:03:10.490
Let's try to open the door.

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:12.620
SHANE SMITH: This was built by
the North Koreans to resemble

00:03:12.620 --> 00:03:13.270
North Korea.

00:03:13.270 --> 00:03:15.760
They wanted it to be like
a home away from home.

00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:19.170
And this was the laboratory
of Kim Il-Sung's theory.

00:03:19.170 --> 00:03:20.595
So we're going to
go check it out.

00:03:28.210 --> 00:03:31.410
So this is where they would
learn about Juche, the ideals

00:03:31.410 --> 00:03:32.840
of Kim Il-Sung.

00:03:32.840 --> 00:03:34.900
The study room was a bit freaky
because it had the

00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:37.650
requisite painting of Mount
Baekdu, which I had seen a lot

00:03:37.650 --> 00:03:40.170
when I was in North Korea, which
was where Kim Jong-Il

00:03:40.170 --> 00:03:42.960
was supposed to have been born
under a double rainbow as a

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.990
new star shot into the sky
to mark the joyous event.

00:03:45.990 --> 00:03:48.910
But in actual fact, he was
really born in a small log

00:03:48.910 --> 00:03:52.180
cabin near Khabarovsk, where
we had started our journey,

00:03:52.180 --> 00:03:55.010
while the Soviets trained his
dad to be the Stalinist,

00:03:55.010 --> 00:03:59.750
cult-of-personality leader of
Korea after World War II.

00:03:59.750 --> 00:04:04.770
So there's a room here filled
with Juche ideals.

00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:07.830
You kind of feel like you've
stumbled on a cult house

00:04:07.830 --> 00:04:11.850
because there's these weird
things to make candles, and

00:04:11.850 --> 00:04:16.640
fires, and homage to the Juche
ideals and we're finding crazy

00:04:16.640 --> 00:04:20.310
propaganda stuff because North
Korea's a cult of personality.

00:04:20.310 --> 00:04:22.755
One man runs, like a
god, the country.

00:04:25.480 --> 00:04:27.380
SIMON OSTROVSKY: It's kind of
got this eerie, Pompeii

00:04:27.380 --> 00:04:28.730
feeling about it.

00:04:28.730 --> 00:04:31.120
SHANE SMITH: It's such a bizarre
concept that there's

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:34.140
little North Koreas dotted
around Siberia.

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:35.550
SIMON OSTROVSKY: This would
have been living quarters

00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:36.480
right here.

00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:37.770
SHANE SMITH: It's
not very nice.

00:04:37.770 --> 00:04:38.890
SIMON OSTROVSKY: Pure filth.

00:04:38.890 --> 00:04:40.140
SHANE SMITH: Very disgusting.

00:04:42.020 --> 00:04:43.270
SIMON OSTROVSKY: There's
one of the old dudes.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:46.800
SHANE SMITH: Oh shit.

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:47.160
Oh that's--

00:04:47.160 --> 00:04:48.210
